> ಮಾರ್ಗ ಮಧ್ಯೆ ಉಪಹಾರ ಮಂದಿರಗಳು / Enroute Refrehment Stops :
> ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ ಸೂಚನೆ / ID Proof Note : 
>           ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್ ಕಾಯ್ದಿರಿಸಿದ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರ ಪೈಕಿ ಒಬ್ಬರು ಪ್ರಯಾಣದ ಸಮಯದಲ್ಲಿ ಪ್ರಸ್ತುತಪಡಿಸಬೇಕಾದ ಮಾನ್ಯವಾದ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿಗಳು :- ಚಾಲನಾ ಪರವಾನಗಿ, ಚುನಾವಣೆ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ, ಪಾನ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್, ಪಾಸ್‌ಪೋರ್ಟ್, ಆಧಾರ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್, ರೇಷನ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್, ಹಿರಿಯ ನಾಗರಿಕರ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ, ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರ ಫೋಟೋ ಸಹಿತ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿಯ ಮೂಲ ಅಥವಾ ಛಾಯಾ ಪ್ರತಿ/ ಸರ್ಕಾರಿ ಇಲಾಖೆಗಳಿಂದ ಫೋಟೋ ಸಮೇತ ವಿತರಿಸಿರುವ ಮೂಲ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ / ಖಾಸಗಿ ಕಂಪೆನಿಗಳಿಂದ ಫೋಟೋ ಸಮೇತ ವಿತರಿಸಿರುವ ಮೂಲ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ/ ಶಿಕ್ಷಣ ಸಂಸ್ಥೆಗಳಿಂದ ಫೋಟೋ ಸಮೇತ ವಿತರಿಸಿರುವ ಮೂಲ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ/ ಫೋಟೋ ಇರುವ ಮೂಲ ಡೆಬಿಟ್/ಕ್ರೆಡಿಟ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್ಗಳು, ಡಿಜಿಲಾಕರ್ ಆಪ್ ಮುಖಾಂತರ ಹಾಜರುಪಡಿಸುವ ಆಧಾರ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್, ಪಾನ್‌ಕಾರ್ಡ್ ಹಾಗೂ ಚಾಲನಾ ಪರವಾನಗಿ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ (ಸಾಫ್ಟ್ ಪ್ರತಿ) ಯನ್ನು ಗುರುತಿನ ಮಾನ್ಯ ಪುರಾವೆಯಾಗಿ ತೋರಿಸಬಹುದಾಗಿರುತ್ತದೆ. Valid IDs to be presented during journey by one of the passenger booked on an e-ticket:- Driving License, Voter Identity Card, PAN Card, Passport, Aadhar, Ration Card, Senior Citizen card with photograph /Original Identity Card issued by the Government Departments with photo / Original with Photo identification card issued by Private Companies/ Original with photo Identity Card issued by the Education Institutions/ Original with Photo debit / credit cards/ Aadhaar, PAN Card and Driving License Identity (Soft Copy) presented through Digilocker App considered as valid proof of identity.
> ವಿಶೇಷ ಸೂಚನೆಗಳು/Important information
> 
> ಹೆಚ್ಚಿನ ವಿವರಗಳಿಗಾಗಿ www.ksrtc.in ನಲ್ಲಿನ ಷರತ್ತು ಹಾಗೂ ನಿಬಂಧನೆಗಳನ್ನು ಅವಲೋಕಿಸಬಹುದಾಗಿದೆ. 
> For details, rules and terms & conditions of E-Ticketing, please visit www.ksrtc.in
> ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್/ಎಂ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್‌ನಲ್ಲಿ ಕಾಯ್ದಿರಿಸಿದ ಆಸನಗಳನ್ನು ಇತರರಿಗೆ ವರ್ಗಾಯಿಸುವಂತಿಲ್ಲ. 
> The seat(s) booked under this e-ticket/m-ticket is/are not transferable.
> ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್/ಎಂ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್‌ನಲ್ಲಿ ನಮೂದಿಸಿರುವ ನಿರ್ದಿಷ್ಟ ಆಸನ ಸಂಖ್ಯೆ ಮತ್ತು ಬಸ್ಸು ಸೇವೆಗೆ ಮಾತ್ರ ಮಾನ್ಯವಾಗಿರುತ್ತದೆ. 
> This e-ticket is valid only for the seat number and bus service specified herein.
> ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿಯನ್ನು ತೋರಿಸದಿದ್ದಲ್ಲಿ ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್‍ನ್ನು “ಪ್ರಯಾಣಕ್ಕೆ ಯೋಗ್ಯವಲ್ಲದ ಟಿಕೇಟ್” ಎಂದು ಪರಿಗಣಿಸಲಾಗುತ್ತದೆ ಹಾಗೂ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರನ್ನು “ಟಿಕೇಟ್ ಇಲ್ಲದೇ ಇರುವ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರು” ಎಂದು ಪರಿಗಣಿಸಲಾಗುತ್ತದೆ. ಇಂತಹ ಪ್ರಕರಣಗಳಲ್ಲಿ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರು ಅದೇ ವಾಹನದಲ್ಲಿ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಸಲು ಇಚ್ಚಿಸಿದ್ದಲ್ಲಿ ಪೂರ್ಣ ಪ್ರಯಾಣದರ ಪಾವತಿಸಿ ನಿರ್ವಾಹಕರಿಂದ ಇಟಿಎಂ ಟಿಕೇಟ್ ಪಡೆದು ಪ್ರಯಾಣ ಮುಂದುವರೆಸಬಹುದಾಗಿರುತ್ತದೆ. 
> E-ticket/m-ticket will become INVALID, if ID proof or e-ticket / m-ticket is not produced and passengers will be treated as 'Ticket without Passenger'. If passengers willing to travel in same service, they can resume their travel by obtaining an ETM ticket from the conductor by paying the applicable fare.
> ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರು ಪ್ರಯಾಣ ಸಮಯದಲ್ಲಿ ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್/ಎಂ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್ ಹಾಗೂ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿಯನ್ನು ಸುರಕ್ಷಿತವಾಗಿ ಇಟ್ಟುಕೊಳ್ಳಬೇಕು. 
> Passenger shall keep the e-ticket/m-ticket safely till the end of the journey.
> ತಪಾಸಣೆ ಸಂದರ್ಭದಲ್ಲಿ ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್/ಎಂ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್ ಹಾಗೂ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿಯನ್ನು ಕಡ್ಡಾಯವಾಗಿ ತೋರಿಸುವುದು. 
> Passenger shall show the e-ticket/m-ticket and ID proof at the time of checking.
> ಹಿರಿಯ ನಾಗರಿಕರ ರಿಯಾಯಿತಿಯು ಕರ್ನಾಟಕ ರಾಜ್ಯದ ನಿವಾಸಿಗಳಿಗೆ ಮಾತ್ರ ಅನ್ವಯಿಸುತ್ತದೆ ಮತ್ತು ಇತರೆ ರಾಜ್ಯದ ಹಿರಿಯ ನಾಗರಿಕರಿಗೆ ಅನ್ವಯಿಸುವುದಿಲ್ಲ. ಹಿರಿಯ ನಾಗರಿಕರ ರಿಯಾಯಿತಿ ಪಡೆದು ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಸುತ್ತಿರುವ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರು ಪ್ರಯಾಣದ ಸಂದರ್ಭದಲ್ಲಿ ಇ-ಟಿಕೆಟ್/ಎಂ-ಟಿಕೆಟ್ ನ ಜೊತೆಗೆ ಈ ಕೆಳಗೆ ತಿಳಿಸಿರುವ ಯಾವುದಾದರೊಂದು ಮೂಲ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿಯನ್ನು ಕಡ್ಡಾಯವಾಗಿ ತೋರಿಸುವುದು. ಚಾಲನಾ ಪರವಾನಗಿ, ಚುನಾವಣೆ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ, ಪಾನ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್, ಪಾಸ್‌ಪೋರ್ಟ್, ಆಧಾರ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್, ರೇಷನ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್, ಹಿರಿಯ ನಾಗರಿಕರ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರ ಫೋಟೋ ಸಹಿತ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿಯ ಮೂಲ ಅಥವಾ ಛಾಯಾ ಪ್ರತಿ/ ಸರ್ಕಾರಿ ಇಲಾಖೆಗಳಿಂದ ಫೋಟೋ ಸಮೇತ ವಿತರಿಸಿರುವ ಮೂಲ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ / ಕರ್ನಾಟಕ ರಾಜ್ಯ ರಸ್ತೆ ಸಾರಿಗೆ ನಿಗಮದಿಂದ ವಿತರಿಸಲ್ಪಟ್ಟ ಹಿರಿಯ ನಾಗರಿಕರ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ/ ಡಿಜಿಲಾಕರ್ ಆಪ್ (Digilocker App) ಮುಖಾಂತರ ಹಾಜರುಪಡಿಸುವ ಆಧಾರ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್, ಪಾನ್‌ಕಾರ್ಡ್ ಹಾಗೂ ಚಾಲನಾ ಪರವಾನಗಿ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ (ಸಾಫ್ಟ್ ಪ್ರತಿ). 
> Senior Citizen concession is applicable for residents of Karnataka State only. Residents of other states are not entitled for Senior Citizen concession. Passengers travelling with Senior Citizen concession need to produce any one of the following Original ID proof at the time of journey - Driving License, Voter Identity Card, PAN Card, Passport, Aadhar, Ration Card, Senior Citizen card with photograph /Original Identity Card issued by the Government Departments with photo / Senior citizen identity card issued by KSRTC / Aadhaar, PAN Card and Driving License Identity (Soft Copy) presented through Digilocker App considered as valid proof of identity..
> ಮುದ್ರಿತ ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್ ನೊಂದಿಗೆ ನಿಗದಿತ ಗುರುತಿನ ಚೀಟಿ ಹೊಂದಿರುವ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರು, ಸದರಿ ಸಾರಿಗೆ ಹೊರಡುವ ಎರಡು ಗಂಟೆ ಮುಂಚಿನ ಅವಧಿಯಲ್ಲಿ ನಗರ ಸಾರಿಗೆ ಸೌಲಭ್ಯವನ್ನು ಉಚಿತವಾಗಿ ಪಡೆಯಬಹುದು (ಹವಾನಿಯಂತ್ರಿತ ಸಾರಿಗೆಗಳನ್ನು ಹೊರತುಪಡಿಸಿ). ಮೊಬೈಲ್ ಟಿಕೇಟ್ (SMS) ಆಧಾರದ ಮೇಲೆ ಉಚಿತ ನಗರ ಸಾರಿಗೆ ಸೌಲಭ್ಯವನ್ನು ನೀಡಲಾಗುವುದಿಲ್ಲ. 
> Free Travel is permitted in City Buses (except A/C buses) within the City limits before 2 Hours of the departure time on production of e-ticket print-outs only. Free travel by showing m-ticket is not allowed.
> ಎಲ್ಲಾ ನಿರ್ಗಮನ / ಆಗಮನದ ಸಮಯಗಳು 24 ಗಂಟೆಯ ಸ್ವರೂಪದಲ್ಲಿರುತ್ತವೆ. ಅಂದರೆ 8:00 AM (ಬೆಳಿಗ್ಗೆ) ಅನ್ನು 08:00 ಗಂಟೆಗಳು ಮತ್ತು 8:00 PM (ರಾತ್ರಿ) ಅನ್ನು 20:00 ಗಂಟೆ ಎಂದು ನಮೂದಿಸಲಾಗುತ್ತದೆ. 
> All departure / arrival timings are in 24 hour format i.e 8:00 AM will be displayed as 08:00 hrs and 8:00 PM as 20:00 hrs.
> ಬುಕ್ ಮಾಡಿದ ಟಿಕೇಟ್‍ನ ವಿವರಗಳು ತಪ್ಪಿದ್ದಲ್ಲಿ ರದ್ಧತಿಗೊಳಿಸಿ ಪುನಃ ಸರಿಯಾದ ವಿವರಗಳೊಂದಿಗೆ ಕಾಯ್ದಿರಿಸುವುದು. ಆನ್‍ಲೈನ್ ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್/ಎಂ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್ ರದ್ಧತಿಗೊಳಿಸಿದ್ದಲ್ಲಿ ಅರ್ಹ ಮೊತ್ತವು ಸಂಬಂಧಪಟ್ಟ ಗ್ರಾಹಕರ ಬ್ಯಾಂಕ್ ಖಾತೆಗೆ ಸಂದಾಯವಾಗಲಿದೆ. ನಗದು ಮೂಲಕ ಯಾವುದೇ ಕಾರಣಕ್ಕೂ ಹಿಂದಿರುಗಿಸಲಾಗುವುದಿಲ್ಲ. 
> If booked e-ticket/m-ticket does not meet passenger requirements, user needs to cancel the ticket and rebook with correct details. Refunds for cancellation of online e-ticket/m-ticket will be made to customer's bank account only. Cash refunds are not allowed.
> ಆನ್‌ಲೈನ್‌ ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್/ಎಂ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್‌ ರದ್ಧತಿ ಮಾಹಿತಿಯನ್ನು ಇ-ಮೇಲ್ ಮತ್ತು SMS ಮೂಲಕ ಖಚಿತಪಡಿಸಲಾಗುವುದು. 
> Cancellation of online e-tickets/m-ticket by the user is confirmed through email and SMS.
> ಪ್ರಯಾಣದ ಸಮಯದಲ್ಲಿ ಇ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್ / ಎಂ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್‍ಗಳನ್ನು ತೋರಿಸದಿದ್ದಲ್ಲಿ ಅಥವಾ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಕ್ಕೆ ಟಿಕೇಟ್ ಬಳಸದಿದ್ದಲ್ಲಿ ಯಾವುದೇ ಮರುಪಾವತಿಗೆ ಅವಕಾಶವಿರುವುದಿಲ್ಲ. 
> No refund is allowed for Not-showing e-ticket/m-ticket or tickets not used for travel.
> ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರು ವಾಹನ ನಿರ್ಗಮನಕ್ಕಿಂತ 10 ನಿಮಿಷ ಮುಂಚಿತವಾಗಿ ನಿಗದಿತ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರನ್ನು ಹತ್ತಿಸಿಕೊಳ್ಳುವ ಸ್ಥಳ ಪಿಕ್‍ಅಪ್ ಪಾಯಿಂಟ್‌ಗೆ ಆಗಮಿಸಲು ವಿನಂತಿಸಲಾಗಿದೆ. 
> Passengers are requested to arrive at the Boarding / Pickup point at least 10 minutes before the scheduled time of departure of service.
> SMS ನ ವಿತರಣೆ (ಎಂ-ಟಿಕೇಟ್‌, ಟ್ರಿಪ್ ಶೀಟ್ ಮಾಹಿತಿ, ಸಾರಿಗೆ ಮಾಹಿತಿ ಇತ್ಯಾದಿ) ಬಳಕೆದಾರರ ಮೊಬೈಲ್ ಸೇವಾ ಪೂರೈಕೆದಾರರ ಮೇಲೆ ಅವಲಂಬಿತವಾಗಿರುತ್ತದೆ ಮತ್ತು ಕರಾರಸಾನಿಗಮವು SMS ವ್ಯತ್ಯಯಕ್ಕೆ ಜವಾಬ್ದಾರರಾಗಿರುವುದಿಲ್ಲ. 
> Delivery of SMS (m-ticket, trip sheet alerts, service alerts etc.) Depends on mobile service provider of the user and KSRTC is not responsible for the delay/ discrepancy in SMS delivery.
> ಟಿಕೇಟ್‌ ರದ್ದುಪಡಿಸುವಲ್ಲಿ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರು ಯಾವುದೇ ಸಮಸ್ಯೆಯನ್ನು ಎದುರಿಸಿದರೆ ತಕ್ಷಣವೇ awatar@ksrtc.org ಗೆ ಇಮೇಲ್ ಮೂಲಕ ವರದಿ ಮಾಡಬೇಕಾಗುತ್ತದೆ. ಅಂತಹ ಮೇಲ್‌ಗಳನ್ನು ಮೇಲ್‌ನ ದಿನಾಂಕ ಮತ್ತು ಸಮಯದ ಆಧಾರದ ಮೇಲೆ ಮತ್ತು ಸೇವೆಯ ನಿರ್ಗಮನದ ಎರಡು ಗಂಟೆಗಳ ಮೊದಲು ಪರಿಗಣಿಸಲಾಗುತ್ತದೆ. ಅಂತಹ ಇಮೇಲ್ ಅನ್ನು ನೋಂದಾಯಿತ ಬಳಕೆದಾರ ಅಥವಾ ಅತಿಥಿ ಬಳಕೆದಾರ ಇಮೇಲ್ ಐಡಿಯಿಂದ ಮಾತ್ರ ಕಳುಹಿಸತಕ್ಕದ್ದು. ನಿಗದಿತ ಸಮಯದ ನಂತರ ಬೇರೆ ಇಮೇಲ್ ಐಡಿಯಿಂದ ಸ್ವೀಕರಿಸಿದ ಇಮೇಲ್‌ಗಳನ್ನು ಮರುಪಾವತಿಗಾಗಿ ಪರಿಗಣಿಸಲಾಗುವುದಿಲ್ಲ. 
> If passenger faces any problem in cancellation of tickets, it needs to be reported by email to awatar@ksrtc.org, immediately. Such mails will be considered based on the date and time of the mail and upto two hours before the departure of the service. Such email shall be sent from registered user or guest user email id only. Mails received after this time or from different email id will not be considered for refund.
> ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರು ತಮ್ಮ ಲಗ್ಗೇಜಿಗೆ ತಾವೇ ಜವಾಬ್ದಾರರು. ಪ್ರಯಾಣದ ಸಂದರ್ಭದಲ್ಲಾಗಲಿ/ವಾಹನದೊಳಗಾಗಲಿ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರ ಲಗ್ಗೇಜಿಗೆ ಕರಾರಸಾನಿಗಮವು ಜವಾಬ್ದಾರವಲ್ಲ. 
> Any personal luggage or belongings should be taken care of by the passengers themselves. KSRTC is not responsible for passenger luggage / personal belongings inside the bus and during the journey.
> ಕರಾರಸಾ ನಿಗಮವು ತಪ್ಪು ಟಿಕೇಟ್ ಹೊಂದಿರುವ/ಸಹ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರಿಗೆ ತೊಂದರೆ ಕೊಡುವ ಹಾಗೂ ಮದ್ಯಪಾನ ಮಾಡಿದ ಪ್ರಯಾಣಿಕರನ್ನು ಪ್ರಯಾಣದರ ಮರುಪಾವತಿ ಇಲ್ಲದೇ ಇಳಿಸುವ ಹಕ್ಕನ್ನು ಹೊಂದಿದೆ. 
> KSRTC reserves the right to off-load passengers who are travelling on incorrect tickets, disturbing co-passengers and also drunken passengers without refund of fare.
> ಬಸ್ಸಿನಲ್ಲಿ ಧೂಮಪಾನ ಹಾಗೂ ಮದ್ಯಪಾನ ಮಾಡುವುದನ್ನು ನಿಷೇಧಿಸಲಾಗಿದೆ. 
> Smoking and consumption of alcohol is strictly prohibited inside the bus.
> ನಿಗಮವು ಸಾರಿಗೆಯನ್ನು ರದ್ದುಪಡಿಸುವ ಅಥವಾ ವರ್ಗ ಬದಲಾಯಿಸುವ ಹಕ್ಕನ್ನು ಕಾಯ್ದಿರಿಸಿದೆ. 
> Corporation reserves the rights to change/cancel the service.
> ಸೂಚನೆ: ಬಳಕೆದಾರರು 'ಯಾವುದೇ ಸಂಸ್ಥೆಯ ಯಾವುದೇ ವ್ಯಕ್ತಿಗೆ ತಮ್ಮ ಆನ್‌ಲೈನ್ ಬ್ಯಾಂಕಿಂಗ್ / ಕ್ರೆಡಿಟ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್ / ಡೆಬಿಟ್ ಕಾರ್ಡ್ ವಿವರಗಳನ್ನು ಹಂಚಿಕೊಳ್ಳಬೇಡಿ' ಎಂದು ವಿನಂತಿಸಲಾಗಿದೆ. ವಿಚಾರಣೆಗಾಗಿ ಕಾಲ್ ಸೆಂಟರ್ 080-26252625 
> All users are requested 'Not to share their online banking / Credit card / Debit card details to any person from any organization. Enquiry 080-26252625.
> 
> ಕಾಯ್ದಿರಿಸಿದವರ ಹೆಸರು/Booked By :	ganeshgadigeppa@gmail.com	ಯಾವಾಗ ಕಾಯ್ದಿರಿಸಿದ್ದು/Booked On :	09-Jan-2024 19:53
>  
> *** ಪ್ರಯಾಣ ಸುಖಕರವಾಗಿರಲಿ/WISH YOU HAPPY JOURNEY. ***
> ಮತದಾರರ ಪಟ್ಟಿಯಲ್ಲಿ ನಿಮ್ಮ ಹೆಸರು ಇದೆಯೇ ಪರಿಶೀಲಿಸಿ, ಇಲ್ಲದೇ ಇದ್ದಲ್ಲಿ ಕೂಡಲೇ ನೋಂದಾಯಿಸಿಕೊಳ್ಳುವುದು

PW Skills Coding Conquest 2023 - Postpon.body:
PW Skills Coding Conquest

🏆 India's Biggest Coding Competition

We hope this message finds you well. As you are aware, the PW Skills Coding Conquest 2023 was initially scheduled for 23rd December 2023. However, after too many requests from students  due to ongoing semester exams in almost all colleges , we find it necessary to reschedule this eagerly anticipated event.

New Date: 14th January 2024, 05 PM to 06:30 PM

Kindly note that the Login URL and the Username and Password for logging in will remain the same for 14th January 2024 as well.

We understand that this change may cause some inconvenience, and for that, we sincerely apologize. Our commitment to providing an exceptional and fair competition experience for all participants remains unwavering. This decision was made with the best interests of all attendees, including students, mentors, and staff, in mind.

The extra time leading up to the new date can be an opportunity for further preparation and practice, ensuring that you are at your best for the competition. We are dedicated to making the Coding Conquest a memorable and enriching experience for everyone involved.

We appreciate your understanding and flexibility. Your enthusiasm and dedication to coding and technology inspire us, and we eagerly look forward to seeing the remarkable talents you will showcase on the new date.

Thank you for your interest in the PW Skills Coding Conquest. We are excited to have you participate in this event!

All the best for your exam!

# Import pandas library for creating tables
import pandas as pd

# Define the cave as a 4x4 matrix of rooms
cave = [[{"room": "[1, 1]", "content": "agent", "breeze": False, "stench": False, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[1, 2]", "content": "empty", "breeze": False, "stench": True, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[1, 3]", "content": "empty", "breeze": False, "stench": False, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[1, 4]", "content": "pit", "breeze": True, "stench": False, "glitter": False}],
        [{"room": "[2, 1]", "content": "empty", "breeze": False, "stench": False, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[2, 2]", "content": "empty", "breeze": False, "stench": True, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[2, 3]", "content": "wumpus", "breeze": False, "stench": True, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[2, 4]", "content": "empty", "breeze": True, "stench": False, "glitter": False}],
        [{"room": "[3, 1]", "content": "empty", "breeze": False, "stench": False, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[3, 2]", "content": "pit", "breeze": True, "stench": False, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[3, 3]", "content": "empty", "breeze": True, "stench": True, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[3, 4]", "content": "empty", "breeze": False, "stench": False, "glitter": False}],
        [{"room": "[4, 1]", "content": "empty", "breeze": False, "stench": False, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[4, 2]", "content": "empty", "breeze": True, "stench": False, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[4, 3]", "content": "empty", "breeze": False, "stench": False, "glitter": False},
         {"room": "[4, 4]", "content": "gold", "breeze": False, "stench": False, "glitter": True}]]

# Define the initial state of the agent
agent = {"position": [0, 0], "direction": "right", "arrow": True, "gold": False, "alive": True, "score": 0}

# Define a function to print the cave as a table
def print_cave():
  # Create an empty data frame
  df = pd.DataFrame()
  # Loop through the rows of the cave
  for i in range(4):
    # Create an empty list for each row
    row = []
    # Loop through the columns of the cave
    for j in range(4):
      # Get the room at the current position
      room = cave[i][j]
      # Create a string to represent the room content
      content = ""
      # If the room contains the agent, add "A" to the content
      if room["content"] == "agent":
        content += "A"
      # If the room contains the wumpus, add "W" to the content
      if room["content"] == "wumpus":
        content += "W"
      # If the room contains the pit, add "P" to the content
      if room["content"] == "pit":
        content += "P"
      # If the room contains the gold, add "G" to the content
      if room["content"] == "gold":
        content += "G"
      # If the room is empty, add "-" to the content
      if room["content"] == "empty":
        content += "-"
      # Add the content to the row list
      row.append(content)
    # Add the row list to the data frame
    df = df.append([row], ignore_index=True)
  # Print the data frame as a table
  print(df.to_string(index=False, header=False))

# Define a function to print the agent's status
def print_status():
  # Print the agent's position, direction, arrow, gold, alive, and score
  print("Position:", agent["position"])
  print("Direction:", agent["direction"])
  print("Arrow:", agent["arrow"])
  print("Gold:", agent["gold"])
  print("Alive:", agent["alive"])
  print("Score:", agent["score"])

# Define a function to move the agent forward
def move_forward():
  # Get the current position and direction of the agent
  x, y = agent["position"]
  d = agent["direction"]
  # Update the position based on the direction
  if d == "up":
    x -= 1
  elif d == "down":
    x += 1
  elif d == "left":
    y -= 1
  elif d == "right":
    y += 1
  # Check if the new position is valid
  if 0 <= x < 4 and 0 <= y < 4:
    # Update the agent's position
    agent["position"] = [x, y]
    # Update the room content
    cave[x][y]["content"] = "agent"
    # Check if the agent is alive
    if cave[x][y]["content"] == "wumpus" or cave[x][y]["content"] == "pit":
      # Set the agent's alive status to False
      agent["alive"] = False
    # Update the score
    agent["score"] -= 1
  else:
    # Print a message that the agent hit a wall
    print("Bump! You hit a wall.")
    # Update the score
    agent["score"] -= 1

# Define a function to turn the agent left
def turn_left():
  # Get the current direction of the agent
  d = agent["direction"]
  # Update the direction based on the left turn
  if d == "up":
    d = "left"
  elif d == "down":
    d = "right"
  elif d == "left":
    d = "down"
  elif d == "right":
    d = "up"
  # Update the agent's direction
  agent["direction"] = d

# Define a function to turn the agent right
def turn_right():
  # Get the current direction of the agent
  d = agent["direction"]
  # Update the direction based on the right turn
  if d == "up":
    d = "right"
  elif d == "down":
    d = "left"
  elif d == "left":
    d = "up"
  elif d == "right":
    d = "down"
  # Update the agent's direction
  agent["direction"] = d

# Define a function to shoot the arrow
def shoot():
  # Check if the agent has the arrow
  if agent["arrow"]:
    # Get the current position and direction of the agent
    x, y = agent["position"]
    d = agent["direction"]
    # Update the position based on the direction
    if d == "up":
      x -= 1
    elif d == "down":
      x += 1
    elif d == "left":
      y -= 1
    elif d == "right":
      y += 1
    # Check if the new position is valid
    if 0 <= x < 4 and 0 <= y < 4:
      # Check if the room contains the wumpus
      if cave[x][y]["content"] == "wumpus":
        # Print a message that the wumpus is killed
        print("Scream! You killed the wumpus.")
        # Update the room content
        cave[x][y]["content"] = "empty"
        # Update the score
        agent["score"] += 1000
      else:
        # Print a message that the arrow missed
        print("Miss! You wasted your arrow.")
        # Update the score
        agent["score"] -= 10
    else:
      # Print a message that the arrow missed
      print("Miss! You wasted your arrow.")
      # Update the score
      agent["score"] -= 10
    # Set the agent's arrow status to False
    agent["arrow"] = False
  else:
    # Print a message that the agent has no arrow
    print("You have no arrow.")

# Define a function to grab the gold
def grab():
  # Get the current position of the agent
  x, y = agent["position"]
  # Check if the room contains the gold
  if cave[x][y]["content"] == "gold":
    # Print a message that the agent grabbed the gold
    print("You grabbed the gold.")
    # Update the room content
    cave[x][y]["content"] = "empty"
    # Update the agent's gold status
    agent["gold"] = True
    # Update the score
    agent["score"] += 100

Important Note:

  *
It is mandatory to attend both assessments to get final assessment marks.

Assessment Schedule:

Final Assessment 1:

  *
2nd March 2024 - Virtual Coding Examination 2 problem statements that have to be solved in 2 hours

  *

Subject: Important Instruction for Final Assessment - Employability Skills-1

Dear Students,

All the students are instructed to attend the final assessments with respect to the Employability Skills-1 course, as mentioned below:

Important Note:

  *
It is mandatory to attend both assessments to get final assessment marks.

Assessment Schedule:

Final Assessment 1:

  *
2nd March 2024 - Virtual Coding Examination 2 problem statements that have to be solved in 2 hours

  *
The total score for this examination will be 10 marks ( 5 marks for each coding question)


Final Assessment 2:


  *
4th March 2024 - MCQ Tab-Based Examination 60 questions on general programming and domain skills

  *
The total score for this examination will be 40 marks.

Please note that the MCQ examination will be a tab-based exam conducted at the college.

The MCQ examination will be conducted as per the timetable attached to this email.

Important Instruction:

  *
In lieu of the upcoming final assessment 1, a practice coding test will be conducted on the Code Tantra platform on February 26, 2024, from 10:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.


  *
You are all required to attend this test without fail because it will prepare you for the final exam, which is scheduled for March 2, 2024.

  *
This test will be web-proctored, and if any student is found to be engaging in malpractice or plagiarism, they will not be allowed to attend the final assessment.

Any doubts related to these assessments can be clarified by visiting the Department of Training & Placement.

Important: Employability Skills - 2 Inst.body:
Dear Students,

Greetings from Dept. of Training & Placement

We would like to inform you all that the Employability Skills - 2 credit course starts from today, 22nd April 2024. This is a one credit course, and it is important for you to meet the eligibility criteria for passing this subject.

All of you are advised to go through the important instructions mentioned below:

  1.
You should maintain a minimum 85% attendance throughout the semester.
  2.
It is mandatory to attend the all the assessments/assignments and evaluations conducted as per the evaluation methodology.
  3.
Do not approach the trainers for any permissions related to absenteeism/late coming. You will have to meet Dr. Saritha Chakrasali, Head Training & Placement regarding the same.
  4.
You should join the WhatsApp group for the program coordination.
  5.
In case if you are unable to join the WhatsApp group kindly come to T&P dept and get added to the group.
  6.
You have to be present in the classroom before the class starts. Any latecomers will not be permitted, and strict actions will be taken against such students.
  7.
Assessments and Assignments will be conducted at regular interval. It is mandatory to attend this as they form a part of your assessment marks. Note the assessments, distribution of marks and minimum requirements are also attached.
  8.
Post the completion of your assessments/assignments and evaluations the marks of the same will be made available to you by the trainer and you will have to check the same and sign the marks sheet without fail.
  9.
In case of any clarifications required in this course meet the T&P department staff between 8:15 to 5:00 p.m. on working days. Do not call or send personal messages to anyone in T&P department. All discrepancies and issues should be reported immediately to the T&P department.

Attached is the syllabus and evaluation methodology for your reference.

Note: All of you should join the WhatsApp group on the link below.

WhatsApp group link: https://chat.whatsapp.com/IChwTeSyZjUJUZzOqeLI72

Addressing by M/s SentinelOne on 3rd May.body:
Dear Students,

M/s SentinelOne is visiting BNMIT on 3rd May 2024 to address the students of 2024 batch. They would like to address 2025 batch students also.

About SentinelOne:
SentinelOne is defining the future of cybersecurity through our XDR platform that automatically prevents, detects, and responds to threats in real-time. Singularity XDR ingests data and leverages our patented AI models to deliver autonomous protection. With SentinelOne, organizations gain full transparency into everything happening across the network at machine speed – to defeat every attack, at every stage of the threat lifecycle.

We are a values-driven team where names are known, results are rewarded, and friendships are formed. Trust, accountability, relentlessness, ingenuity, and OneSentinel define the pillars of our collaborative and unified global culture. We're looking for people that will drive team success and collaboration across SentinelOne. If you’re enthusiastic about innovative approaches to problem-solving, we would love to speak with you about joining our team!

All of you are eligible to for the same. Eligible CGPA is 9.0 above

Interested eligible students should register on the link given below by the end of day.

Link: https://forms.gle/b9cArb27NnmaVG4EA

Virtual Internship Program by M/s Salesf.body:
Dear Students,

M/s Salesforce is hiring for Virtual Internship Program for 2025 students.

This Virtual Internship will be providing learners with valuable industry knowledge and hands-on experience along with networking opportunities.

Virtual Internship Tracks:

  *
Salesforce Administrator: | Branch: All | CGPA: >6.5 or >65% | Other Skills: Both Coding and Non coding background students |
  *
Salesforce Developer:  | Branch: AlI - Recommended CSE, ECE and IT etc. | CGPA: >6.5 or >65%| Other Skills: Basic Programming Knowledge, object-oriented programming language and language to manage data held in a relational database management system

Virtual Internship Program details:

  *
120 hrs. of overall learning experience
  *
Hands-on Bootcamps, Project work and Mentoring support
  *
Acquire Super Badges on Trailhead platform
  *
Receive Virtual Internship Completion Certificate
  *
Students can submit the certificate to apply for academic credits subject to approval from College/university or affiliated state/central university as per UGC/AICTE norm and guidelines.
  *
Develop interview skills through an exclusive soft skills training
  *
Access to career fair with networking opportunities (via Interested Partners)
  *
Get prepared for Salesforce Professional Certifications

Interested students should register on the link below by the end of the day.

Link: https://forms.gle/rnb5mrXLN9WSHQmZA

Dr. Saritha Chakrasali
Head, Training & Placement
[cid:099f0527-1b6e-43eb-a88d-0515c5faa587]
Vision: ​  ​To be one of the premier institutes of Engineering and Management education in the country.
​​Mission: To provide Engineering and Management education that meets the needs of human resources in the country.
​            ​    To develop leadership qualities, team spirit and concern for environment in students.

Urgent: 10 SECONDS Pre-Assessment.body:
Dear Student,

*Greetings from 10 SECONDS, your placement training partner at BNMIT. *

As part of your credit course, it is mandatory for you to attend the
assessments. Below are the details of the pre-assessment for your
reference. Please complete your tests before the deadline, as no extensions
will be granted.

Post completion of the Pre-assessment, we will mail you about the lined-up
Mock assessments

*Before the test begins, kindly ensure that all students thoroughly review
the user manual. The manual is designed to be self-explanatory and
addresses many common issues that might arise.*
__________________________________________________________________
______________________

PRE-ASSESSMENT | BNM
Test Opening Time:17-5-2024 18:00
Test Closing Time:20-5-2024 23:45
Test Duration:30.00 mins
College/Course:BNMIT / BE
Test Link:
https://learning.10seconds.co.in/test/683b6646-aaca-4936-8ad2-8b51cf99bf0d
__________________________________________________________________________________

*Instructions:*
1) Ensure that there are no spaces at the beginning or end of your email
when you type it.
2) Use the email and phone number you provided during registration as your
first time login credentials.
3) Note that switching tabs or automatic screen turning off on your mobile
device will trigger an automatic submission of your form.

If you encounter any problems, please send an email to
shreejeshballal@gmail.com with cc to pavan@10seconds.co.in with relevant
screenshots, College name, your USN, full name, email address, and a
detailed description of the issue. Tech team will not respond to inquiries
lacking these details.

Thanks and regards,

Team - LMS
10 SECONDS

I recently had the incredible opportunity to attend the 10-day Bug Bounty Course at Ibby Cybersecurity, led by the brilliant Dr. Mohamed Ibrahim. This intensive program was a deep dive into the exciting world of ethical hacking, vulnerability assessment, and advanced cybersecurity techniques. Dr. Ibrahim's expertise and engaging teaching style made every complex topic feel accessible and practical.

This course has not only enhanced my technical skills but also ignited a greater passion for cybersecurity. I'm eager to apply these skills in future projects and contribute to a safer digital world.

Sudha R shared a post: 🌟 The Heart of Leadership: Boss vs. Leader 🌟
The distinction between a boss and a leader can shape organizational success profoundly.
A boss delegates tasks, but a leader delegates authority, empowering their team to take ownership and excel. A boss manages resources, while a leader cultivates talent and fosters professional growth.
True leadership extends beyond directives; it's about fostering a culture of collaboration, trust, and continuous learning. Leaders lead by example, demonstrating integrity, empathy, and a commitment to collective achievement.

Dear Students,

This is with reference to the industry internship hiring by M/s Betsol.

All of you are instructed to carefully go through the details mentioned below and register for the same if you are interested.


  *
Position Requirements:

     *
Product Security Position: 6th semester students
     *
Project Position: 4th & 6th semester students
  *

  *
Eligibility Criteria:

     *   No active backlogs.
     *
75% and above in academics.

  *
Interview and selection date: Tentatively on 12th June, Wednesday
  *
Program Start Date: Tentatively on Monday, 17th  June 2024
  *   Target Branches: BE/B.Tech in CS, IS, AI & ML branch
  *
NDA document: NDA must be signed by the selected students as the part of the onboarding process

Registration Link: https://forms.gle/mgm6LQ9ue3qFSDjH9
Google Forms: Sign-in<https://forms.gle/mgm6LQ9ue3qFSDjH9>
Access Google Forms with a personal Google account or Google Workspace account (for business use).
forms.gle

  *
The registrations have to be completed before 5th June 2024.

Dr. N Sheshaprasad IEEE photonics EXECOM Member shared a post: #mystudentmystrength
#myteachingmystrength
1-8-2002 - the day my journey with BNMIT began! ✨

Today, I'm filled with gratitude as I celebrate an incredible 22 years as a faculty member in the ECE department at BNMIT. This milestone also marks 25 years in academia overall! 🎓

It's been an extraordinary experience shaping young minds and witnessing their growth. I'm truly fortunate to have worked alongside such talented students and dedicated colleagues.

Beyond academics, I've been privileged to contribute to our vibrant campus culture. As an active mentor of Kalabhageerathi, the cultural club, I've had the opportunity to foster creativity and artistic expression among students. Additionally, my involvement with the BNM Friends of Nature club has allowed me to instill a deep appreciation for our environment. 🌱

A big thanks to our esteemed Chairman, Sri. Narayan Rao R Maanay sir, Director Prof. T J Ramamurthy sir, Deputy Director Dr.krishnamurthy GN sir, Principal and Additional Director Dr.S.Y. Kulkarni Sir, Dean and Trustee Prof Eishwar Maanay sir for their unwavering support and guidance.

Here's to many more years of learning, inspiring, and contributing to BNMIT's bright future! 🚀

#Education #BNMIT #Gratitude #TeachingJourney #Milestone #ThankYou #ECE #22Years #Academia #FacultyLife #Kalabhageerathi #BNMFriendsofNatureclub #inclusiv

BNM Institute Of Technology Prof Eishwar Maanay Vaishnavee Maanay Sowmya Narayanan Sadagopan Dr. Yasha Jyothi M Shirur Dr. Chaitra N Dr. Vijayashree Lakshman Saritha Chakrasali Satheesh Kumar Inclusiv

M/s Synamedia is hiring 2025 batch students.

The Job description is attached for your reference.

Job Details:
Designation: Associate Software Engineer
Location: Bangalore
Fixed Salary: 6,50,000 INR + (Variable pay: 7%, Sign on Bonus: 75,000 INR)

Eligibility: B.E. - CS/IS/AIML/ECE with 7.0 CGPA (No Backlogs) and 70% in 10th, 12th/Diploma.

Hey there!

Do you love learning and have a passion for a particular subject? Ever wished you could share your insights and experiences with others?

We have an exciting opportunity for you! You can use the Blog feature on Infosys Springboard and fulfill your writing desires!

[cid:image002.png@01DAB8D7.28AD5AE0]


You can blog about sharing your study habits, how to master a complex life situation, a book review, your experience on Infosys Springboard and how has it helped you learn? The possibilities are endless!

Getting started on your writing journey is super easy!


  *   Login to Infosys Springboard<https://infyspringboard.onwingspan.com/web/en/page/home>
  *   Access blogs by clicking on the following link - Blogs on Infosys Springboard<https://infyspringboard.onwingspan.com/web/en/app/social/blogs_v2/view-blogs>
  *   Click on 'Write a blog' on the top right and you're all set to begin your writing journey.

We can't wait to see your amazing content!

Happy learning and happy writing,

Infosys Springboard Team

Your Android devices will soon join the.body:
The Find My Device network is coming soon



You can use Find My Device today to locate devices when they're connected  
to the Internet. With the new Find My Device network, you'll be able to  
locate your devices even if they're offline. You can also find any  
compatible Fast Pair accessories when they're disconnected from your  
device. This includes compatible earbuds and headphones, and trackers that  
you can attach to your wallet, keys or bike.

To help you find your items when they're offline, Find My Device will use  
the network of over a billion devices in the Android community and store  
your devices' recent locations.

How it works

Devices on the network use Bluetooth to scan for nearby items. If other  
devices detect your items, they'll securely send the locations where the  
items were detected to Find My Device. Your Android devices will do the  
same to help others find their offline items when detected nearby.


Your devices' locations will be encrypted using the PIN, pattern or  
password for your Android devices. They can only be seen by you and those  
you share your devices with in Find My Device. They will not be visible to  
Google or used for other purposes.


You'll get a notification on your Android devices when this feature is  
turned on in three days. Until then, you can opt out of the network through  
Find My Device on the web. Your choice will apply to all Android devices  
linked to talavarakshatha57@gmail.com. After the feature has been turned  
on, you will be able to manage device participation at any time through the  
Find My Device settings on the device.

Learn more











You received this email to update you about important changes to your  
Android device.

© 2024 Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA

Infosys Springboard Pragati: Path to Fut.body:
[cid:image001.png@01DABC29.0813FE60]






Dear Learner,



We are delighted to inform you that our Infosys Springboard Pragati: Path to Future Cohort 1 is nearing its conclusion, and we are thrilled to announce the opening of registrations for the July-September cohort. This is an exclusive career development program for women which will be anchored every 3 months.



The program will cover the following four key areas:

Self-Growth


Professional Advancement


Career Development


Leadership Skills




Click here to register<https://infyspringboard.onwingspan.com/web/en/page/embed-gno?survey=2117>




We would also like to share some feedback that we have received from Cohort 1 participants:



I'm thrilled to share my thoughts on the Pragati program! Participating in this program has been a truly transformative experience for me. The courses offered through Infosys Springboard are outstanding - they are thoughtfully structured, easy to follow, and packed with valuable content. Each module has provided me with new insights and deepened my understanding of key concepts. One of the aspects I appreciate most is the balance between learning and assessment. The assessments are not just a measure of what I've learned; they challenge me to apply my knowledge in practical scenarios, which has greatly enhanced my critical thinking and problem-solving skills. Being on the leaderboard has been incredibly motivating. It's a tangible acknowledgment of my hard work and progress, and it inspires me to keep pushing myself further.

Overall, the Pragati program has been more than just an educational experience; it's been a journey of personal and professional growth. I'm grateful for the opportunity to learn, grow, and achieve through this wonderful initiative. Thank you for providing such a supportive and enriching platform!

  *   Gajja Poojitha




My first offer is with Infosys but due to personal reasons I couldn't make it up. From that moment, associating with Infosys was my dream which came true through Pragati. The modules and sessions attended so far are very much interesting. We can see 250+ plus participants attending every session with such interactions and that too after the busy work hours seems a kind of motivation. Very happy to be a part of the Pragati Program.

- Jeevitha Palanisamy




The key factors that have contributed to my success in Pragati: Path to Future program are consistency and smart work. The personality development courses offered during this program have been invaluable in enhancing my skills in communication, leadership, and emotional intelligence. The interactive sessions and expert mentorship have provided guidance on handling professional and personal challenges effectively. Through Agile Practices, I have gained insights into Agile systems and gained hands-on experience in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning. Padma Bhamidipati Ma'am has been a truly inspiring figure, known for her professional excellence and dedication in the industry. I am highly satisfied with the quality and content of the program . I look forward to continuing my learning journey and contributing to the success of the Pragati Program. I commend the Infosys Springboard team for their unwavering dedication, support, and guidance throughout the program.

  *   Kanike Shruthi






Through this program we aim to address essential competencies like Digital Dexterity, Gen AI Fluency, Professional Skill Enhancement, Leadership Acumen, Domain Awareness, and Industry Engagement.



Few points to remember:



     *   This program is exclusively for women aged 18 and above, including students, young professionals, job seekers, or those considering re-entering the workforce.
     *   The program will follow a hybrid model, with one week out of the 12 held at various Infosys campuses and offices. The remaining 2.5 months will be conducted virtually.
     *   Registration by males will be automatically cancelled.



What's next?



  *   We will review your application and if shortlisted, we will reach out to you for a quick discussion.
  *   To be eligible, you must be a registered learner on Infosys Springboard with at least one course completion.
  *   Once selected, we will share the complete program schedule for both in-person and virtual sessions. The schedule for in-person sessions will be shared based on the city you select in your registration form.

Dear Students, Job Seekers, and Working Professionals,
 
Unlock Your Potential with iPEC's Latest Courses in AI & ML, Data Science, and Business Data Analytics!
Are you ready to elevate your skills and embark on a journey of professional growth? iPEC, Bangalore, is thrilled to present our latest courses in Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning (AI & ML), Data Science, and Business Data Analytics, designed to empower students, job seekers, and working professionals like you.
Why Choose iPEC?
Cutting-edge Curriculum: Our courses are crafted with the latest industry trends and technologies, ensuring you receive a comprehensive and up-to-date education.
 
Experienced Faculty: Learn from seasoned professionals and experts in the field, gaining insights from their real-world experiences.
 
Practical Hands-on Experience: Acquire practical skills through hands-on projects, case studies, and industry-relevant assignments, preparing you for the challenges of the workforce.
 
Industry Connections: Benefit from our strong network of industry partners, opening doors to internship opportunities and potential job placements.
 
Flexible Learning Options: Whether you are a student, job seeker, or a working professional, our courses offer flexible schedules and online learning options to suit your needs.
 
Courses Offered:
 
Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning (AI & ML):
 
Explore the fundamentals of AI and ML algorithms.
Hands-on experience with industry tools and frameworks.
Gain insights into real-world applications of AI & ML.
 
Data Science:
 
Master the art of extracting valuable insights from data.
Learn statistical analysis, data visualization, and predictive modelling.
Apply your skills to solve complex business problems.
 
Business Data Analytics:
Understand the role of data analytics in business decision-making.
Develop proficiency in data-driven decision strategies.
Analyze and interpret business data for strategic planning.
Join iPEC and transform your career in the dynamic fields of AI & ML, Data Science, and Business Data Analytics. Whether you are a student aiming for a strong foundation, a job seeker looking to stand out in the market, or a working professional seeking career advancement, our courses are tailored to meet your unique aspirations.
 
Visit our website at www.ipecsolutions.com  to explore detailed course outlines, admission procedures, and exciting opportunities that await you. Don't miss out on the chance to enhance your skills and shape a successful future!
 
For inquiries, contact us at 6366373030, 6366791314
Empower your future with iPEC – Where Innovation Meets Excellence!

Connect over music – with loved ones near or far
Is there a special song that always reminds you of someone? Or a melody  
that transports you back to when you first heard it? Music is more than  
just entertainment: it shapes our connection with the world. From finding  
forgotten tunes to sharing cherished songs, your  
Android<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5q3V_-FgjxU6cgUTmJhVtAVxv_HVRGkPBBTf_GeAwSlgPbz9EaV49f_v5zl0EsHP07xSvcsBwopoHJcMQ6cpww_98XCBLcwVm12ODuqmk7sLkcUb5ncfZPh5Xjjl_9ifS44sJqKxodAMjnt83wqvRktLPOdlsb9_hHeL86HLs9dA3zV8tIy69ZCKiyxm8_R68Op4BKwHmrc7wEXaIz5NLScGfdwKme7KIj_j15ogn_Rpu6bqghb1mC_MGWScwAxcZh0pHivWQGCVCxY2kLQ3bMY4RYjmDw3lObaRX1ZdSZ9>  
phone helps to amplify our passion for music – connecting people near and  
far.
<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5qWxAQdBCiKk9usk7SRNHEtPpboDe6OU_YICv7LaliJS2YdnitdLcMpNGFu1d9gbg33ogaBbb4svO-2bgccmRiA2Twmep6dyKNDtKH07U-IuaKEtph7SnXWuEfSbU4uuaGKqhbbFBuRjixKY1IWq3Xcxm7b10RwSd9cS8_BYM6x1i3Dgc8PXxPuwPiN1w9FeFDFBlne9y7Mh-ArsU0V4Jqb7f2BQN-3pFyrVnnlA-Hj6_z3pBeEjIHFjLRZBWF3r_oYPKvCW0M-UPPIPcNDV24VTRRoMRuh_68F8fnNDyc_0l7wfIsK_PxlV2WoBzSTB4cENMlXWaQtT8CrJOUEx9uil1xph4RySIO-QF4TqAsuIOSuvgNe2MlJYg>

Turn that forgotten tune into a weekend anthem

You know that song that goes 'da na naa naa'? Well, now you can search for  
it with just a hum or a whistle. Just tap the 'Search a song' button in  
Google  
Search<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5pxQXuQkZFRb4jWlY-y-lDYYo_PjjB5c-EojSyGBTKprox2wXlwaJR6urVr2wKha3ogJtPtkEJo4ADyNXdBd00C5S3xDQOjnV1aHayqaKrvsDkTdQoA1yFZvq2b_bjGuhJtDn3XSm2vpgb49u1y3WdiY5JR_ydZSKEddrrZLq0r4SRzui5qLS5jY-4WvG9sHESV3-cRE1CLvfz9qjWD-9DIWGQjm_VZfXChjhoPdg7Pu6-cGur3S4AxezigPa4980o-KTR5W6SCilkdmPi4Cdls6CNXdRWwglmR_A4fa3d8sIpwUhTnnWA_qqbGb5A8>  
and hum 10–15 seconds of the tune – no lyrics, artist name or perfect pitch  
required. You'll receive a list of likely matches, which you can explore  
and listen to.

Learn  
more<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5oz5pwap1hTnim12gUuGyI9vD4tA9Yh0i8j7E6KUSRPziWXxdJByZJ_4ur8RN4T2Up6sJu9Cg6HFgbLj7ZiLv_tOX5f8ny2XvDZ0yHTXVMhPDN-surQ0ZepZlJmKfQ8KFOeleQ91ZAoa_A1LB0n3HPcoHd3sV19oCBM8QnMeN-YalcXJRJAVapgVCsSlIx4UH3ISR4uYISWxBHJR6ZnX8t-4DnGlqVasrLeXwXGrwtcmEDLlopOfq9TLY1ljoh2V09XffDL_P-FqmA06fv4t_ofFRlKs_DMt1ZyJ6HCOehGwuomYqZZGgkFNO1Ht1-C>

Ditch the paper tickets for digital versions

Have you remembered the tickets? From stadium concerts to intimate jazz  
clubs, Google  
Wallet<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5oIwm3I_UXnQYeP20jUzRIGpasM70r9l1RlSvb9X_OoxoVJ-GqSwHJAZc9W1d3knqBBzYH1osfMggsOiyOrV2W7loHPZhlOVRLkDsShk-lI0wUTGd24ny7QZLqI_vrKUs3SEz3lLiefKnsz_k3FCFadfZOH8jljOgKVT2EGO_Ccet7NF_vp_s4oK1zJcvRObN04Qfo-1XVS-HXWokweG6__3_anWn_FDGJpGNOuuUBRbmsYB83m3zM7-M1xYqW6vxIv3IQeS_WXOEt00T1aUze69FWdo7QTTUlWtu5MhxVmsuekGg>  
passes make it easier to carry tickets with you – whatever your jam. Add  
digital copies of event tickets for quick access, and if the ticket isn't  
compatible with Google Wallet, you can scan the barcode or QR code to keep  
a digital version with you.

tickets<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5o0a3QYUdPFL9IJ9WB15sbqWCTuRaoF5SJG3ZzbgaYJkimuM-25C9V9qnrQZaWlbkv1_4ens5NuZhKu_G0kN7uWFN6HThfsRLU08skvnONbMFxtDpOMwZlrZdsUQDJynRmh4ZLCoiaQ5T5X36zpRfuCGSEI8splVrO63SJeiu1qrDQgJHk_Gi_FLyZ_zZLLw7UCRA7gfTAHyrMtvGvj_Td1S3xNSm96yn4nD1IMvsx7U8g4L49ep1V0RgLM3OkSwpF0ipGoNJL2P6OJbZsr497DfDXhjdj3e0clY-18hTQBzdUp0nGbbwk7ldf2Lo8M-IIMgRZWszgS>

Placement Policy and Declaration form fo.body:
Dear Students,

Greetings from the Department of Training & Placement!!

The Training & Placement Department is happy to announce the Campus Recruitment for the Batch of 2021-25 which will be conducted during your pre-final and final year.

It is strictly advised to actively participate in all the activities to become eligible for most of the companies that visit BNMIT for Campus Recruitment 2024-25.

All the activities shall be conducted in three phases as mentioned below during your 6th, 7th & 8th semesters.

  *
6th semester - Training & Development activities (Employability Skills 2 Credit Course, Pre-Placement Training, Cocubes Assessment, Company Specific Training & Assessments)
  *   7th semester - Campus Recruitment activities (Hiring by Service, Product & Dream Companies)
  *   8th Semester - Intensive Student Development & Recruitment activities (Intensive training for yet to be placed students, company orientation programs, internships & Core Company hiring)

Attached is the Placement Policy and Declaration Letter.

Note:

  *
You are advised to go through the attached 'Placement Policy - 2025' & 'Declaration Form'.

  *
You should take a printout of Declaration Form, read it carefully and sign it. Also, you are required to get it signed by your parents without fail and upload the scan copy of signed Declaration Form on the link given below before 28th June 2024.

      Link: https://forms.gle/jQMsp8BE1P273k1L7

  *
Students who are not willing to participate in the Campus Placements - 2024 are informed to submit a letter for the same signed by you and your parents on 27th June 2024 to the T&P department.

Important Instructions:

  *   It is mandatory to attend the Pre & Post Assessment Tests.
  *   It is mandatory to maintain a minimum of 85% attendance during the Pre-Placement Training program.
  *   It is mandatory to maintain discipline during the Pre-Placement Training program. Any misbehavior during the program will be considered seriously and necessary actions will be taken against such students.
  *   You have to be punctual in the training program.
  *   Any student violating the instructions of the T&P Department / Trainers during the program will be suspended from the training program.

Dr. Saritha Chakrasali
Head, Training & Placement
[cid:2744e343-6e9d-4744-b34a-3d9a45b363b8]
Vision: ​  ​To be one of the premier institutes of Engineering and Management education in the country.
​​Mission: To provide Engineering and Management education that meets the needs of human resources in the country.
​            ​    To develop leadership qualities, team spirit and concern for environment in students.

________________________________
From: NDLI CLUB <ndl.club@iitkgp.ac.in>
Sent: Thursday, June 20, 2024 5:02 PM
To: Library (Undergraduate) BNMIT <library_ug@bnmit.in>
Subject: NDLI Club presents an event Global Event : Afternoons with an Author - "Vyomesh Shuklas critically acclaimed non-fiction book on Varanasi, Aag Aur Pani, published by Rukh Publications"

[https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21694263/65243751-9655c180-db06-11e9-9b57-b83e9d0286b9.png]

Dear Dr. R. M. Puttaswamy,

Your NDLI Club has created an event on Global Event : Afternoons with an Author - "Vyomesh Shuklas critically acclaimed non-fiction book on Varanasi, Aag Aur Pani, published by Rukh Publications". The event details are mentioned below and you are requested to encourage all the students and faculty members of your institute to join this event:

Event Date and Time: Sun Jun 30, 2024, 04:00 PM .

Event Location: https://www.youtube.com/live/kPq_HHp93Rw?si=78QWS5eoLAx57bMb .

Event Description: NDLI in collaboration with the Valley of Words present the next edition of Global Event: Afternoons with an Author - "Vyomesh Shuklas critically acclaimed non-fiction book on Varanasi, Aag Aur Pani, published by Rukh Publications". Featured Speaker: Vyomesh Shukla, Poet, Essayist, Critic, Translator and Director Moderator: Dr. Sanjeev Chopra Author, Historian, Policy Analyst, Columnist and Festival Director of Valley of Words Lead Discussant: Professor Pravin Kumar, Renowned Author ABOUT THE EVENT June edition of Afternoons with an Author will discuss Vyomesh Shuklas critically acclaimed non-fiction book on Varanasi, Aag Aur Pani, published by Rukh Publications. Award-winning Vyomesh Shukla is a poet, essayist, critic, translator and director. He started his writing career in 2004. He is listed among the best writers and personalities shaping India's socio-cultural landscape. Vyomesh manages the 'Roopavani Reportry' in Varanasi, directing numerous plays. His work revolves around presenting new interpretations of Ramayana and Mahabharata while preserving traditional craftsmanship. The author will be in conversation with Assistant Professor, award-winning author Pravin Kumar. Praveens collection of stories, Chhabila Rangbaaz Ka Shahar, Amar Deswa and Vasco da Gama Ki Cycle, have been widely acclaimed. He is known for his use of new narrative language and innovative techniques in story writing. The session will be moderated by Sanjeev Chopra, Festival Director of Valley of Words. You have to attend the Event by visiting this YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/live/kPq_HHp93Rw?si=78QWS5eoLAx57bMb We request you to participate in the event and encourage other NDLI Club members of your institute to join this event. You can download the Certificate of Participation after a day of the session. For any queries, please write to club-support@ndl.gov.in Thanks and Regards NDLI Club Central Team.

For Registration, existing NDLI Club members of your institute can click on the Member Login<https://u4465288.ct.sendgrid.net/ls/click?upn=u001.60YJKKO-2BdVEKZL1Y4rD3gEXhn6RuJ6Cf2X298CeJlXwImCD6FZ0YYEKqCQst3ktjaJEg_-2Fjtq6ossq9WcBPNoq-2FwhgcPaRFAYgfGTWLJRFZES1WcyI9cTB8tdnuW-2BOkFuXdRVc0qjSzJxfJdMnn82caOL0LZMqUUpyvo7l8mPuzq62gBvrD03bJ-2BgsBdcyHlBxKxhbGaV9v0WJXXEBiY2TOu5PBSNia-2FgF5nYiwul6n0WdZLE8X28W4zUwDZTfm66QO5aK4aCMT7j698wdi4hoparmkjO-2F0EX1guW6L-2BG-2FrsK9mZ-2FKa1TLiSUyzOlCli-2BRZFvVjdHSW6ZN9GGxHg4gslHzVByJ5eP9088PlN3pi8a8QuGgBqtToninNVwrdEYlLTbpR48toSr3lRHyyn-2BItogcNrDFiH2JSmgUSh3DPld8XL-2Bvd3j-2BKaawr-2BSwSF8HMdN>. Then they have to enter their NDLI Club registered eMail ID (Username) and Password. After logging-in, click on the Events section and select the event name. Then check the Eligibility button available at the right side of the event. Once it shows, you are Eligible, then Click on the Participate button.

If any new students/ faculty members of your institute who are not members of the NDLI Club want to join the session, then they should join the NDLI Club first by using the NDLI Club Unique Passkey and then register themselves. Applications for Software Engineering by.body:
Dear Students,

M/s Google India is hiring 2025 batch students for Software Engineering role - Off Campus.

Interested students should go through the details below and register on the link.


[Screen Shot 2016-05-10 at 12.41.14 PM.png]
[https://lh7-us.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfibM_AbLmfBJAxiiuCD2nq6AA3ZMOc0BTwY-LLiQZRYty_MuqXBxvKVjPBMr9mG0WUwY5uyxZ4E0YnqBpCkFcc9yA9xPkCI2e3XcnX9cf1jbWtNFjPD5go6muiefopv3rovKuiNcqcF7uvVsC35B5_ytEkzyYt5ELcbBCrpRO_IEgUtUrZwQ3q34Qh-_v2BjA?key=uEB9SCw4UqIcqneCNY2GBA]


Google is and always will be an engineering company. We hire people with a broad set of technical skills who are ready to tackle some of technology's greatest challenges and make an impact on millions, if not billions, of users. At Google, engineers not only revolutionize search, they routinely work on massive scalability and storage solutions, large-scale applications and entirely new platforms for developers around the world. From AdWords to Chrome, Android to YouTube, Social to Local, Google engineers are changing the world one technological achievement after another.

In this regard, we are happy to share that we have opened up applications for our 2025 graduates for Full Time Employment (FTE) Off Campus Opportunity for the below role:

Apply Now: Software Engineering, University Graduate, 2025<https://goo.gle/NG2024>

We encourage the students to apply directly on the Google Careers page and our recruiting team will get in touch with the candidate directly.

Meanwhile, find below few other opportunities to engage with Google:

  *   Google Summer of Code<https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/programs/2023/organizations> - A global, online mentoring program focused on introducing new contributors to open source software development.

  *   Google Conference Scholarship<https://buildyourfuture.withgoogle.com/scholarships/google-conference-scholarships> - Scholarships to attend selected conferences in the tech industry and related fields

  *   Grow with Google Career Certificates<https://grow.google/intl/en_in/certificates/> - Professional training designed by Google and the opportunity to connect with top employers

  *   On Demand Learning Content<https://careersonair.withgoogle.com/#student_events> - Readily accessible content for students to learn and engage with

=?UTF-8?q?NEW_partnerships,_exciting_upd.body:
-----------------------
Another exciting month!
-----------------------

This month, we released heaps of new rooms and challenges, and two very exciting modules!

 

Also... we're going to Vegas! 🇺🇸

We can't wait to see you at Black Hat and DEF CON. Keep scrolling to find out where you can meet us and pick up some free swag 😉

Continue learning ( https://tryhackme.com/recommend/last-room?utm_source=email_marketing&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=monthly )

*******
New in:
*******

****************
NEW! Snyk module
****************

We’ve partnered with Snyk, a renowned player in DevSecOps! This partnership brings a NEW DevSecOps module developed by Snyk experts.

Launch Snyk module → ( https://tryhackme.com/module/snyk?utm_source=email_marketing&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=snyk )

****************
NEW! Careers Hub
****************

Uncover careers in cyber security and receive comprehensive advice on how to achieve these careers. We have you covered every step of the way!

Launch Careers Hub → ( https://tryhackme.com/r/careers?utm_source=email_marketing&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=careers_hub )

****************************
NEW! Cyber career match quiz
****************************

Wondering which career is right for you? Take our quiz to discover your perfect cyber career match. It only take a few minutes!

Take career quiz → ( https://tryhackme.com/r/careers/quiz?utm_source=email_marketing&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=careers_quiz )

*****************************************
NEW! Module: Advanced Server-Side Attacks
*****************************************

Master the skills of advanced server-side attacks, covering SSRF, File Inclusions, Deserialization, Race Conditions, and Prototype Pollution.

Launch module → ( https://tryhackme.com/module/advanced-server-side-attacks?utm_source=email_marketing&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=advanced_server_side_attacks )

****************************************
Introducing our updated 'navbar' search!
****************************************

A new search tool is here, providing you with a quick and easy way to search for content directly from the navbar!

Explore search page → ( https://tryhackme.com/r/hacktivities/search?page=1&utm_source=email_marketing&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=updated_navbar )

*************************
Black Hat & DEF CON 2024!
*************************

*************************
Black Hat & DEF CON 2024!
*************************

Join us in Vegas for Black Hat (booth 2841) between the 7th-8th of August, and DEF CON between 8th-11th August. You'll get to meet the TryHackMe founders and room creators, connect with other members of the community, and grab some free swag. See you there! 🇺🇸

************
New training
************

( https://tryhackme.com/r/room/xxeinjection )XXE Injection

Recognise concepts and dangers associated with XXE injection.

( https://tryhackme.com/r/room/tsharkthebasics )TShark: The Basics

Learn the TShark basics and take your protocol and PCAP analysis skills a step further.

( https://tryhackme.com/r/jr/clusterhardening )Cluster Hardening

 Learn how to secure network traffic on a Kubernetes.

Discover new training ( https://tryhackme.com/r/hacktivities/search?page=2&kind=rooms&order=relevance&roomType=walkthrough )

**************
New challenges
**************

( https://tryhackme.com/jr/include )
( https://tryhackme.com/r/room/airplane )
Discover new challenges ( https://tryhackme.com/r/hacktivities/search?page=1&kind=rooms&order=relevance&roomType=challenge )

*************************
TryHackMe for School 🏫
*************************

Need fun labs to give to students in your classes? Assign security labs & challenges.

* Student Management
* Over 640 Reusable Labs
* Real-world Challenges and Networks
* Student progress insight
Spend less time creating exercises and more time teaching. We will even suggest content for your courses!

Email education@tryhackme.com

Launch TryHackMe Education ( https://tryhackme.com/classrooms )

*****************************************************************
TryHackMe for Business 💼 ( https://emojipedia.org/briefcase/ )
*****************************************************************

Upskill your workforce with gamified hands-on training, featuring realistic security lessons for all skill levels.

* Custom Team Learning Paths
* Transferable Licenses
* Reporting and Insights
* Dedicated Success Manager
Join hundreds of organisations upskilling their workforce with TryHackMe.

Email sales@tryhackme.com

Launch TryHackMe Business ( https://tryhackme.com/business )

****************
We're hiring ✨
****************

TryHackMe is continuing to experience rapid growth, and so we're looking for talented individuals to join our team and help over three million users learn cyber security!

Full Time Remote Positions 

 

Creative Designer ( https://www.notion.so/Creative-Designer-f25cf66502f148dd91179bbe3d6e594d?pvs=21 ) to create vector-based illustrations, character designs, and animations for various teams at TryHackMe.

 

Content Engineer ( https://tryhackme.notion.site/Content-Engineer-Blue-Team-0d342735633546ebbc9db51ca438865d ) to build (blue team) defensive training content.

 

Product Designer (6 Month FTC) ( https://tryhackme.notion.site/Product-Designer-6-month-FTC-3f38d4ff39854f6495e83daa9f4ba6e2 ) to design, prototype and develop new product solutions.

 

Senior Software Engineer (12 Month FTC) ( https://tryhackme.notion.site/Senior-Software-Engineer-12-Month-FTC-0f2ee5c847254291852cf05e72fcdb36 ) to scale TryHackMe to support millions of users. 

 

See other open roles ( https://tryhackme.notion.site/Careers-at-TryHackMe-6bd665d7bd3448348d04fa06f4b4ef66 ) →

TryHackMe Employment Benefits

* Competitive Salary
*
401k / Pension and Health Insurance
* $2,000 Dedicated training budget
* Flexi time & fully remote
* Annual company retreat
* Flexible career and learning development
Newest Team Members

* Cami, Head of Marketing
* Filip, Software Engineer
* Tom, Content Engineer Manager
* Oussama, Software Engineer
Thank you for reading!

=?UTF-8?Q?Sudha_R_shared_a_post:_Burnout.body:
Sudha R shared a post: Burnout in the workplace: a silent epidemic that's impacting us more than we realize.
As professionals, we often pride ourselves on our dedication and work ethic. But behind the scenes, burnout can quietly erode our productivity, creativity, and even our mental health. It's a challenge that doesn't discriminate based on industry or seniority—it affects us all.
In today's fast-paced world, the lines between work and personal life are increasingly blurred. The pressure to constantly perform, coupled with the expectation of being always available, can take a toll. Recognizing the signs of burnout early is crucial, not just for our well-being but also for maintaining sustainable career growth.
#Burnout #WorkplaceWellness #EmployeeWellBeing #WorkLifeBalance #StressManagement #MentalHealthAtWork #HealthyWorkplace #CareerDevelopment #ProfessionalGrowth #SelfCare

Claude Pro and Team users can now organize chats into Projects. Projects bring together internal knowledge and chat activity in one place so Claude can help you generate ideas, make strategic decisions, and deliver exceptional results.

Tejas Nagaraj Hegde shared a post: 🌟🌟🌟 #DevStudioCon2024 : A Thriving Tech Event in Bengaluru by Wix

Wix Studio - DevStudio_Con in Bengaluru, India, was a resounding success. The event showcased Wix's comprehensive suite of features and apps designed to empower developers, entrepreneurs, leaders, and businesses to achieve growth and prosperity.

Had a wonderful time at the pre-event chatting with Hitesh Choudhary about career diversity and growth strategies!

The opportunity to connect with industry leaders and engage with Wix's latest innovations was exceptional. 

A special thank you to Vargab Bakshi for his outstanding leadership in driving the event, along with the insightful keynote speakers. I am also grateful for the opportunity to connect with exceptional individuals from Wix and the broader tech industry, including:

Even-Haim Yaniv / CTO, Wix  
Yoav Abrahami / Head of Code Products, Wix  
Vargab Bakshi / VP Head of India, Wix  
Hana Siani Cohen / Head of Wix Blocks at Wix.com  
Uval Blumenfeld / Head of Product - Wix Mobile App Builder  
Tuvit Rubin-Kaplan / Head of Developer Relations, Wix  
Daniel Orsher / Product Manager, Wix Code, Wix  
Hiran Dash / Partnerships & Localisation Head, India  
Saurabh Rajpal & Anchit Nishant / Staff Web Ecosystem Consultant & Cloud Architect, Google  
Varun Mayya & Tanmay Bhat / Overpowered AI YouTube Channel  

🌟🌟🌟 Major insights & Key Takeaways:

💎 Leveraging Technology for Efficiency: Artificial intelligence (AI) and cutting-edge technologies offer significant opportunities to optimize workflows and enhance operational efficiency.

💎 Full-Stack Wix Development Expertise: Agencies and developers can leverage Wix Blocks, Wix Apps, Wix Mobile Apps, Wix Enterprise, Wix Studio and more to create comprehensive solutions.

💼 The panel moderated by Kobi Gamliel featured Dhairya Chheda, Jonathan Lopes, and Andrei Homorodean, sharing strategies for maximizing profitability in dev shops and web agencies.

🛠 Workshop Highlights:

1. Building an e-commerce storefront with Next.js and React.js by Netanel Gilad from Wix
2. Developing apps on your terms with Wix CLI by Adir Amsalem
3. Working effectively alongside your designer by Yakir Mordehay and Eden Apelboim – special thanks for their patient guidance and insightful responses during this session. Had a lot to learn!!

Thank you to everyone who made #DevStudioCon2024 a memorable and insightful event. Looking forward to future collaborations and innovations in the tech industry!

It was my pleasure connecting with talented individuals like Pranav N, Ishaan Choubey, Praveen Gouda, Jogesh Rajiyan, vaishno raj, Pranav Subramaniyan R, Anagha Karwa, Soumik Mitra and Saibala Sundram at the event. Your insights and perspectives added immense value to the discussions.

#DEVSTUDIO_CON #Wix #DevStudioCon2024 #WixStudio #Innovation #AI #TechLeadership #WebDevelopment #Technology #Growth #WixBlocks #TechEvents #ITCompanies #BusinessNetworking

Updates to our terms for AI.body:
We recently announced a beta for AI features in Figma Design. In this email, we are sharing our approach to building AI [https://www.figma.com/ai/our-approach/?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tos&utm_content=inline_ai_features] features and what's next.

To improve these features, we plan to start training AI models to understand design concepts, patterns, file structure, and tooling in Figma. Learn more about how your team can manage AI and our other updates below.

MANAGING AI SETTINGS

Team admins can control how their teams use AI with two new settings for each
team they manage:

 * Whether your team can use AI features (on by default for Starter and
   Professional teams).
 * Whether content is shared for AI training (on by default for Starter and
   Professional teams).

AI features and content training are optional. Teams can use AI features, even if content training is turned off. Read how to access your AI settings here
[https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/17725942479127-Control-AI-features-and-content-training-settings?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tos&utm_content=inline_ai_settings].

The content training setting goes into effect on August 15th, 2024. If an admin turns off content training after that, new content and edits will not be used to train AI models.

NEW AI TERMS IN OUR POLICIES

The key updates to our Terms of Service [https://www.figma.com/legal/tos/?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tos&utm_content=inline_tos]
and Privacy Policy [https://www.figma.com/legal/privacy/?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tos&utm_content=inline_privacy] do the following:

 * Allow Figma to use your team's content to improve AI features, when content training is set to 'on'
 * Clarify that you retain your rights to content inputted into Figma AI and to the results generated

These new terms will go into effect on August 15, 2024. By continuing to use Figma, including keeping your files with us, you agree to these terms.

If you'd like to read more about Figma's approach to AI, please visit our website [https://www.figma.com/ai/our-approach/?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tos&utm_content=inline_ai_website].

Thank you for using Figma.

The Figma team

Note: This is a legal notice, which is why you are receiving it even if you have opted out of Figma marketing and promotional emails. Replies to this email are
not being monitored. Visit our Help Center to learn more.

Figma is a design platform for teams who build products together. Born on the Web, Figma helps the entire product team create, test, and ship better designs, faster.

Welcome to the CodeChef community.body:
Hey Akshatha Talavar,

I am really happy to know that you have joined CodeChef.

CodeChef is on a mission to help you learn and practice computer science in the most fun and engaging way.

A lot of students ask me for advice on how to use CodeChef or learn programming in general.

At CodeChef, we always had an opinionated view on this. We think that you learn best by applying what you have learned. Most students I see keep taking one course or another but can never actually retain the content after the course is over.

On CodeChef you will find less theory and a lot of practice, so that you never forget what you learn.

If you don't know programming start with any programming language course, because that is the first step. Then go on to learn logic building, data structures, algorithms, etc.


You can find all our courses here - https://www.codechef.com/learn


All of these courses are free to preview, but you have to buy Pro to complete the course and gain a certificate. We have put a lot of hard work in building these courses, and hope you will love them.


Regards,

Aniruddh

Product Head - CodeChef

Mock placement drive and Evaluation.body:
Dear Students,

A company simulated online assessment will be conducted between 8th and 12th July 2024,post 6pm. as part of Mock placement drive.

The scheduled date and time will be shared. The test will include aptitude and technical questions.

Mock GD and Personal Interviews are scheduled on Saturday, 13th July 2024 (8:30am to 5pm).

This is a part of your credit course assessment and will be graded.

Important Instructions:

  *
All of you should report 5 minutes early to your allotted time.
  *   you should wear business formals for the process.
  *   you should compulsorily carry the below documents:
     *   2 sets of photocopies of your marks cards (10th, 12th & B.E.)
     *   2 copies of your updated resume
     *   Copies of your ID & Address proofs

Note:

  *
This is a part of your evaluation and is a mandatory requirement for passing this credit course. Attendance is mandatory.

Dr.Sheshaprasad N shared a post: 🚀#Disability: A Facet, Not a Definition

Disability. Just a word, right? But in our world, it often becomes the defining characteristic, overshadowing the multifaceted individual beneath. It's like focusing solely on someone's eye color or height, ignoring the rich tapestry of their personality and achievements.

✅ I've never viewed my disability as something to be ashamed of. It doesn't diminish my worth or the value I bring to my loved ones and colleagues. My contributions as a researcher, teacher, leader, and mentor stand on their merit, independent of any disability label.

✅Society often perpetuates myths about disability, resorting to euphemisms like "specially-abled" or "differently-abled" that do little to change the underlying perceptions. These labels don't erase the challenges I face nor capture the essence of who I am.

✅ Let's break free from these boxes! Instead of labels, ask me directly about my needs, preferences, and aspirations. It's not about empty platitudes or celebrating us in separate categories.
✅ We, as people with disabilities, crave genuine inclusion. Treat us as equals, just like anyone else. Recognize an artist for their creativity, a singer for their voice, or an athlete for their skill, regardless of disability.
✅ That's when we can truly be "disabled and proud." We are proud of who we are, our achievements, and our contributions. And that, in turn, is a source of pride for everyone.

#ConversationsAroundDisability #DisabilityPrideMonth #DisabilityInclusion #DisabilityAwareness

🚩P.S. My story, of overcoming challenges and achieving success with a disability, exemplifies the power of resilience and the importance of an inclusive environment. Let's work together to create that world!

Hiring Women in tech 2024: Synamedia.....body:
[Careers@Synamedia]<https://my.synamedia.com/sites/careers/sitepagemodern/22270/careers-home>

At Synamedia, we're not just imagining a brighter future, but boldly creating it. That is why we are committed to empowering more women to join and thrive in the tech industry. In fact, we are proud of the fact that over 40% of our grad hires in the last two years are women.



We value a bold approach and a bias to action besides, of course, deep curiosity to learn and grow. Our Early-In-Career program is designed to fuel your growth and success by empowering you with tools and opportunities that make you ready to lead.



We invite you to apply for our Technical Graduate Programme and join us in disrupting the industry with innovation and passion.
[https://tvmc.stripocdn.email/content/guids/CABINET_10af81e6a6351213cb9c0488cb0271e2dcaa9b3097914e4cf242a0cef02642f3/images/nidhi_srivastava.png]

Nidhi Srivastava, Associate Software Engineer Bangalore (Joined Synamedia: 2023)



Recently, we had a Campus to Corporate training that helped new graduates like me transition smoothly from academia to the workplace. There are various networking events like hackathons that provide female employees with opportunities to connect and build professional networks.

To support work-life balance, Synamedia offers flexible working hours, hybrid work options, and inclusive parental leave policies. Regular diversity and inclusion training sessions ensure a respectful and supportive workplace, reflecting Synamedia's commitment to fostering an environment where women in technology can thrive.

Nagaratna Patil, Manager, Technical Writing, Bangalore (Joined Synamedia: 2017)



"Synamedia is a great place for women in tech due to its strong commitment to diversity and inclusion, with zero-tolerance policies for discrimination and bias.  We are offered inclusive mentorship programs, and encouraged to attend industry events to expand professional networks.
[https://tvmc.stripocdn.email/content/guids/CABINET_10af81e6a6351213cb9c0488cb0271e2dcaa9b3097914e4cf242a0cef02642f3/images/nagaratna_utN.png]

Additionally, flexible work arrangements, comprehensive training opportunities, and regular pay equity audits empower female employees to thrive and lead in their careers."



Click the 'Apply now' button to join a team of winners and a workplace that truly makes you feel cared about.


Apply now
[https://tvmc.stripocdn.email/content/guids/CABINET_10af81e6a6351213cb9c0488cb0271e2dcaa9b3097914e4cf242a0cef02642f3/images/footer.png]


Sincerely,
The Synamedia Recruitment Team

Dear Students,

This is with reference to the AON Cocubes Y-1 assessment to be conducted as a part of your continuous evaluation.

The same will be conducted on Saturday, 13th July 2024.

Note:

  *
The test window will be open from 10:00 a.m. To 7:00 p.m. It is instructed that all of you complete the same at your convenience, without fail.

It is mandatory to complete this test.

Dear Students,

This is with reference to the hiring by M/s Accenture.

All of you are instructed to fill the details required for M/s Accenture drive in the below form.

Link: https://forms.gle/d6C6wJ16PpbCfCvP9

Instructions to fill the form:

  *
Name should be as per PAN Card (First and Last Name should be more than or equal to two alphabet)
  *
In case you do not have Last Name, mention your Father/Mother's Name as specified in your PAN Card

Note:

  *
You should fill the form mandatorily before 2:00 p.m. today.
  *
If you do not fill the form you will not be eligible to participate.

Eligibility Criteria :


  *
Minimum criteria- Any engineering stream of B.E/B.Tech with year of passout being 2025.
  *   No active backlogs during application and/or during onboarding.
  *
Students must have Indian citizenship.
  *
Candidate’s PAN Card with photo is mandatory to register for the process.
  *
E-PAN is Valid only at the time of Registration. At time of joining, original pan card is mandatory.
  *
Candidate should not have appeared for Accenture Recruitment assessment/interview process in the last three months.
  *
Candidate should have completed the relevant degree in the stipulated duration of the degree. Hence, there should be no gaps during the course of your degree. E.g. candidate must complete the 4-year B. Tech course in 4 years.


Dr. Saritha Chakrasali
Head, Training & Placement

CoCubes Assessment || CoCubes 1 || Test.body:
Dear Candidate,

Your management has decided to conduct your upcoming CoCubes assessment from home on 14th July 2024 to ensure your safety.


As a mandatory step in the process you are required to complete the online assessment of six sections (Aptitude, Psychometric, WET, Computer Fundamental, Coding and Domain ) in single sitting.


Please find below the assessment details and instructions.


  *   Test Link: https://assess.cocubes.com
  *   System Check Link: https://assess.cocubes.com/check-system  (Please run this on your systems before beginning with the assessment).
  *   Activation Pin: 45304

  *   Passkey 1-  ( For Aptitude, Psychometric, WET, Computer Fundamental, Coding): 119656

  *   Passkey 2-  ( For Domain): 251696
  *   Test Time: 10:00 AM to 07:00 PM (You must login between this window only) Note: You will have next 6 hours to complete the assessment after the activation of the assessment.

Click Here<https://drive.google.com/file/d/1xpccuE3wVPyzw2iUW2xpYDVahH5YCnzI/view?usp=sharing> to view the video to understand the flow of the assessments.

Click  Here<https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1YtRfkhCBj3Cn3TdDHECE2Eyh2y7pQjnw?usp=sharing> to view syllabus and FAQ.

Click Here<https://drive.google.com/file/d/1yKutkXqLPJBoGqrbTK-QNbffD4IuoPM0/view?usp=sharing> if you don't have Username and Password or you forgot password.

It is mandatory to complete all the sections with both Passkeys, only then your report will be generated.

Steps to appear for the assessment:


  *   Enter the Test Link URL.
  *   Enter Username, Password & Assessment Passkey.
  *   Click on Start Test.
  *   Enter the Activation Pin.
  *   Click on start assessment to begin the test
  *   After completing the assessment with Passkey 1 login again with Passkey 2 and complete the domain test.
We don't recommend the test from the mobile phone, since the assessment has two topics which are descriptive in nature (WET & Coding)
[cid:image001.png@01DA7C7A.9FB40380]
Other Important Instructions

  *   In the case of Internet failure, the test will continue to run, and you can attempt the questions without any hassles. As soon as the internet is resumed, all answers get saved automatically.
  *   In case of power failure, do not panic, restart the test using the same link, and the same browser, the test will start from the same question which you had left earlier, and all attempted questions remain attempted and responses gets saved.
  *   If you have any query during the online test, please drop an email to aasindiaqueries@aon.com<mailto:aasindiaqueries@aon.com> and call on the below number to get your query addressed quickly.
  *   Usage of Mobile phones, electronic gadgets, calculators are strictly prohibited.
  *   In Case any candidate is found be copying via online proctoring, the monitoring team will give you max time warning and the information for the same will be passed onto the CoCubes team and you will be disqualified immediately and logout from the exam in the rear time..
  *   Using other websites during online test can be captured through online monitoring, so refrain yourself from doing the same. If any candidate found using other websites will be disqualified immediately.
  *   You need to take up the test in a single sitting. You are not allowed to move during the test.

*Note: Please reach out 7000903208 if you face any problem during the test.


Stay safe & healthy!


Regards,
Team Aon
